description: Around 200 encroachers, allegedly of Bangladeshi origin, attacked members of the Lucknow municipal corporation near Shubh Marriage Lawn in Indiranagar on Sunday. The assault forced the team, led by supervisor Meenakshi and food inspector Vijeta Dwivedi, to retreat. Subsequent to the incident, LMC demolished approximately 50 illegal huts near Indiranagar police station.
title: Encroachers attack Lucknow civic body staff, 2 hurt
2 fall into molten metal at Chhattisgarh factory, killed

description: Protesting farmers at Khanauri, Punjab, increased security around fasting farmer leader Jagjit Singh Dallewal in response to the government's potential efforts to provide medical aid. Volunteers are on guard, conducting checks, and have secured the area with welded tractor-trailers. Farmers called for a Punjab bandh on Dec 30, supported by various societal sections.
title: Farmers up Dallewal 'security' as SC pushes Punjab for medical aid

description: Nathan Lyon and Scott Boland's resilient 50-run partnership for the final wicket frustrated India, extending Australia's lead to over 300 runs on day four of the Boxing Day Test. Their defiance marked only the second instance of a 10th-wicket pair batting for over 50 balls in both innings in Test history, turning the tide at the Melbourne Cricket Ground.
title: MCG magic! Lyon, Boland revive Pakistan's 1961 feat vs India

description: A study by IIT-Kharagpur highlights the financial challenges faced by Integrated Command and Control Centres (ICCCs) in 100 smart cities due to inadequate funding from states and municipalities. The report recommends revenue sharing, monetisation of infrastructure, and capacity building to support ICCCs' sustainable operation and maintenance.
title: Smart cities staring at financial crisis; control centres being bled dry: Study

description: As the Dalai Lama's 90th birthday approaches on July 6, speculation rises about whether he will announce his successor, a move likely to heighten tensions with China. With the Panchen Lama in Chinese custody, the process of validation is complicated, and he may also declare an end to reincarnations.
title: Will Dalai Lama name successor on birthday?

description: A car accident in southern Ethiopia's Sidama region has resulted in the deaths of 66 people, with four others receiving treatment at Bona General Hospital. The incident occurred at Gelana bridge in Bona Zuria Woreda. The Sidama Regional Health Bureau is investigating the cause and has offered condolences, with further details to be provided soon.
title: At least 66 killed in southern Ethiopia road accident, health authority confirms

description: Former US President Jimmy Carter, known for championing human rights and global peace, has died at 100. He served from 1977 to 1981 and was awarded the Nobel Peace Prize in 2002 for his humanitarian efforts. Carter was in hospice care and surrounded by family at his passing.
title: Former US president Jimmy Carter passes away at 100
New mom made to travel 100km in Maha due to lack of ICU, dies
Mason’s son beats Covid, cash crunch to clear CA exam, builds hope for kin

description: PM Narendra Modi, during his 'Mann Ki Baat' address, urged the nation to use the Maha Kumbh in Prayagraj as a platform for unity, highlighting the event's role in fostering national cohesion. Scheduled from Jan 13 to Feb 26, 2025, the Maha Kumbh will include digital navigation aids and AI chatbot services to assist visitors.
title: Kumbh an occasion to foster unity, eliminate hatred: PM Modi

description: Tigress Zeenat, who had wandered from Odisha's Similipal on December 8, was tranquillised and captured in Bengal's Bankura village after evading forest officials from three states for 21 days. Following a nearly 300km journey, she was taken to Kolkata's Alipore zoo for a health check before being returned to Similipal.
title: 21 days on, wandering Odisha tigress sedated, captured in Bengal village

description: Karnataka high court ruled in favor of a teenage rape survivor, deeming paternal consent for her child's adoption irrelevant. The court emphasized the need for a loving environment for children of incapable guardians, defining them as orphans and ensuring their right to live with dignity.
title: Rape accused's nod not must for kid's adoption, says HC

description: Navi Mumbai International Airport will be inaugurated on April 17, with public access starting in May and international flights by July. The new greenfield airport aims to alleviate congestion at Mumbai airport, initially handling 10-12 million passengers per annum with future expansion plans.
title: After first civilian test flight landing, Navi Mumbai airport set for May ops

description: Police suspect the Nov 24 violence in Sambhal was orchestrated by absconding gangster Shariq Satha, linked to Dawood and Pakistan's ISI. Unusual money transfers and foreign-made cartridges were found, indicating his involvement. Shariq, who has 54 cases against him, is wanted in multiple states and fled to Dubai in 2020 using a fake passport.
title: Gangster with ‘Dawood-ISI links’ plotted Sambhal violence: Cops
Three MMR institutions play a key role in PSLV with cutting-edge experiments

description: Jammu's deputy chief minister, Surinder Choudhary, condemned the proposed ropeway project in Katra, arguing it threatens 40,000 livelihoods. The town, a base camp for the Vaishno Devi pilgrimage, remained shut in protest. Choudhary urged the shrine board and lieutenant governor to heed local concerns and highlighted the risk to key spiritual sites.
title: Katra protest against ropeway enters 5th day, BJP MLA also joins in

description: The search for missing 22-year-old student Santra Elizabath Saju from Kerala ended in tragedy as a body believed to be hers was found in Almond river, Edinburgh. Santra, a student at Heriot-Watt University, was last seen on Dec 6 in Livingston. Her family has been informed, and police do not suspect foul play.
title: Missing Kerala student found dead in Scotland

description: Sepoy Solomon from Manipur, despite his home being destroyed by a mob, successfully passed the Army Cadet College exam and Services Selection Board interview. He is now on the path to becoming an officer, a first from his village. With support from his battalion, his journey is an inspiration of determination.
title: Home destroyed by mob during conflict, Manipur sepoy to be Army officer

description: Sara Arfeen Khan was evicted from Bigg Boss 18 after a heated altercation with Karan Veer Mehra, reducing the contestant pool to ten. The eviction stirred significant reactions, further accompanied by a contentious debate between Kashish Kapoor and Avinash Mishra, which host Salman Khan addressed.
title: BB 18: Sara Arfeen Khan gets eliminated, show gets top 10 contestants

description: Ankur Jain, an American entrepreneur, founded Bilt Rewards, which is valued at $3.1 billion. Jain, previously VP of products at Tinder, sold his app Humin to Tinder. He married former WWE wrestler Erika Hammond in 2024 after they met at Rumble Boxing gym. Jain’s estimated net worth is $1.2 billion.
title: Who is Ankur Jain? Billionaire’s son with $1.2 bn net worth and WWE wife

description: A massive underwater landslide, found in the Krishna-Godavari basin between 950m and 1.1km below the ocean surface, poses a significant risk to underwater structures and coastal inhabitants. The landslide, caused by events like Cyclone Helen and earthquakes, moved around 11 cubic km of sediments, potentially triggering a tsunami.
title: Underwater Krishna-Godavari basin landslide can trigger tsunami: Scientists

description: Sunil Gavaskar criticized Rishabh Pant for attempting a risky shot out of ego in a crucial moment during a Test match, mentioning that Pant's approach was unnecessary given the situation. Gavaskar emphasized that Test cricket is challenging and highlighted the importance of playing smart. Meanwhile, Marnus Labuschagne's 70 helped Australia recover from a collapse, giving them a 333-run lead.
title: Sunil Gavaskar clarifies context of 'stupid' remark for Rishabh Pant

description: Patna police used water cannons and mild-lathi charge to disperse BPSC aspirants protesting for a re-exam of the 70th BPSC prelims at Gandhi Maidan. Despite police urging to vacate, students continued their protest, supported by Prashant Kishore of Jan Suraj, who criticized the Bihar administration for inhibiting their right to public demonstration.
title: Police lathicharge, use water cannons on protesting BPSC aspirants

description: Excerpts from a diary reportedly found on a deceased North Korean soldier in Russia’s Kursk region offer a rare glimpse into the mindset and tactics of North Korean troops allegedly fighting alongside Russian forces. The diary released by the Ukrainian forces reveals loyalty to Pyongyang, battlefield struggles, and controversial tactics.  Ukrainian officials estimate that thousands of North Koreans are deployed, with heavy casualties reported.

description: Elon Musk supports Poornima Ramarao's appeal for an FBI investigation into her son, Suchir Balaji's death. Ramarao disputes the suicide ruling, providing evidence of a struggle and demanding justice. The case has garnered support from AI ethics advocates and tech industry figures.

description: China has introduced the CR450 prototype, the world's fastest high-speed train, achieving test speeds of 450 km/h. This innovation emphasizes safety, energy efficiency, and passenger comfort. Featuring advanced technology, the CR450 is poised to enhance China’s leading position in global rail transport, with possible commercial operations beginning next year.

description: Congress MLA Uma Thomas sustained severe head and spinal injuries after falling from the Jawaharlal Nehru International Stadium gallery in Kochi. She is currently in critical condition, receiving treatment in the ICU with ventilator support. Medical experts are being consulted to determine further treatment plans.
title: Congress MLA falls from stadium gallery in Kochi, condition critical

description: Poornima Ramarao, mother of Suchir Balaji, seeks FBI investigation into his death, alleging foul play despite police ruling it a suicide. A private autopsy revealed discrepancies, and family efforts include legal action and public campaigns to prompt a proper investigation.

description: India face a challenging 333-run target against Australia on Day 5 of the fourth Test at MCG. The weather is expected to remain mostly favourable, with minimal chances of rain disruption. Temperatures will range between 25°C to 27°C, and conditions will be partly sunny with significant cloud cover. Fans anticipate an intense, uninterrupted day of Test cricket.

description: India's Yashasvi Jaiswal dropped three catches on Day 4 of the Melbourne Test against Australia, resulting in visible frustration from skipper Rohit Sharma. Rohit's reaction was criticized by commentators, suggesting the need for calm support. Rishabh Pant's encouraging response was praised for uplifting Jaiswal's spirits.

description: Indian-American Congressman Shri Thanedar faced online abuse and calls to 'go back to India' after advocating for increased H-1B visas and streamlined processes. Highlighting xenophobia within extreme MAGA circles, Thanedar argued that attracting legal, talented immigrants benefits the US, countering claims that foreign workers undercut American wages.

description: South Africa secured their place in the World Test Championship Final by defeating Pakistan in the first Test of the two-match series. The Proteas chased down a 148-run target on the fourth day, solidifying their top spot in the WTC standings. They will face one of Australia or India in the WTC Final at Lord's in June.

description: Delhi Police are investigating alleged data collection for the AAP's 'Mahila Samman Yojna' scheme after concerns raised by Congress' Sandeep Dikshit. Lt Governor Saxena directed an inquiry into improper personal information gathering. The Delhi government departments have denied the existence of such a scheme, distancing themselves from AAP's claims as elections approach.

The victory, driven by tail-enders Kagiso Rabada and Marco Jansen, confirmed their top-two finish in the standings. The achievement follows their 2-0 win over Sri Lanka and improved their percentage points to 66.67%.

description: Azerbaijani President Ilham Aliyev accused Russia of shooting down an Azerbaijani passenger plane, killing 38 of 67 passengers. Aliyev demanded an apology, acknowledgment of guilt, and compensation. Survivors reported loud noises, and the Kremlin admitted active air defence systems. Investigations are ongoing with a joint probe at the crash site.

description: Norovirus outbreaks are rising sharply across the United States this winter, with 91 outbreaks reported in early December, compared to 69 in late November. Known for causing sudden vomiting and diarrhoea, norovirus spreads easily, especially in crowded settings. With no specific treatment, prevention through hygiene remains the best defence. Here’s what you need to know.

description: Elon Musk endorsed Germany's far-right Alternative for Germany (AfD) in an op-ed, calling it the country's "last spark of hope." In 2021, Germany's domestic intelligence agency labelled the AfD a suspected extremist organisation at the national level.

description: Mark Zuckerberg, Meta CEO, has clarified that the underground structure on his $270 million Hawaiian estate is a practical shelter, not a high-tech Doomsday bunker as rumored. The main purpose of the ranch is to produce world-class beef, not secretive survival preparations.
title: Doomsday bunker under Facebook founder Mark Zuckerberg, here's the truth

description: President-elect Donald Trump has backed Elon Musk's support for the H-1B visa program, despite previous opposition. Trump's endorsement has caused a rift among his supporters. Big tech figures such as Musk argue that the program is essential for maintaining US industry leaders.

description: Jasprit Bumrah and Mohammed Siraj led India's attack brilliantly on the fourth day of the Boxing Day Test. Bumrah's standout performance, including his 200th Test wicket, and Siraj's increased speed helped dismantle Australia's middle order. Omarzai's all-round performance and Rutherford's batting prowess also stood out across their respective matches in 2024.

description: South Africa secured their place in the World Test Championship Final by defeating Pakistan in the first Test of the two-match series. He accused Russia of hiding the crash's cause and noted the plane encountered 'external interference' in Russian airspace. Russian President Vladimir Putin apologized but did not assume responsibility.

Taking 36 wickets in 18 matches, his performance in the T20 World Cup final highlighted his skills. Competing with Sikandar Raza, Travis Head, and Babar Azam, Arshdeep’s achievements solidify his importance in India’s T20 team.

description: Nitish Reddy silenced critics with a century at the MCG, scoring 114 runs and bringing India's total to 369. Team India remains optimistic for a comeback.

The plane skidded off the runway due to landing gear failure and struck a concrete barrier. Initial reports suggest a bird was stuck in the wing. Opposition parties rejected Kavelashvili's legitimacy. The Georgian Dream party's increasing authoritarianism and delayed EU membership discussions have fueled ongoing demonstrations, despite widespread public support for EU integration.

description: A Jeju Air flight from Bangkok crashed at Muan International Airport in South Korea, likely due to bird strike and adverse weather. description: A Jeju Air flight from Bangkok to South Korea crashed while landing at Muan Airport, likely due to bird strikes and adverse weather. The crash resulted in 151 confirmed deaths out of 181 people onboard. Rescue efforts and an official investigation are ongoing.

description: The India vs Australia fourth Test witnessed a record Boxing Day Test attendance with 299,329 fans. It surpassed the previous highest of 271,865 set during the 2013 Ashes Test. description: Jasprit Bumrah's 4-56 and a milestone 200th Test wicket gave India hope on Day 4 of the Boxing Day Test, but Australia's lower-order resistance, led by Marnus Labuschagne and Pat Cummins, held firm. description: BJP criticized Congress for allegedly politicizing the death of former PM Manmohan Singh, rebutting claims about the funeral's arrangements. The BJP cited adherence to state protocol and security restrictions while Congress accused BJP of showing disrespect and disrupting the proceedings. Both parties exchanged accusations over the events following Singh's death.

description: When Russia invaded Ukraine in 2022, Indian cricketer Nitish Kumar Reddy's sister, Tejaswi, was stranded but safely returned to India. She transferred to a university in Uzbekistan. The family continues to cherish these memorable moments.

description: Google CEO Sundar Pichai urged employees to focus on AI competition and regulatory challenges by 2025, emphasizing the importance of scaling the Gemini AI model. An investigation into the tragedy is underway.

description: Yashasvi Jaiswal faced a challenging Day 4 in the Boxing Day Test after dropping three important catches, including Marnus Labuschagne's edge. description: Gorakhpur govt railway police dismantled a gang of mobile phone thieves led by Manoj Mandal from Jharkhand. Police recovered 44 mobile phones worth Rs 10 lakh from them.

description: PM Modi emphasizes the importance of the Constitution and announces a nationwide campaign to read the Preamble. Emergency services reported that the shark bit him on the neck, causing fatal injuries. This incident is part of the ongoing tally of shark incidents in Australia, with more than 250 fatalities recorded since 1791.
title: Australia: Man killed by shark while fishing with family

description: Mohammed Siraj dismissed Usman Khawaja and signaled Australian fans to 'keep quiet' amidst their booing following a previous clash with Travis Head. Australia reached 53 for 2 at lunch, leading by 158 runs. Nitish Kumar Reddy scored a century for India, aiding his team to reach 369 before falling to Nathan Lyon. Nitish has accumulated 293 runs so far in his maiden Test series.
title: DSP Siraj tells booers in Melbourne to keep quiet - Watch

description: On Sunday at Melbourne Cricket Ground, Nitish Kumar Reddy's father showed respect to Sunil Gavaskar by touching his feet after Nitish scored a century in the fourth Test against Australia. Nitish’s crucial hundred and partnership with Washington Sundar bailed India out of trouble. Nitish currently tops India's batting chart in the series while Australia's Travis Head leads overall.
title: Watch: Nitish's father touches Gavaskar's feet, gets a warm hug

description: A Jeju Air Boeing 737-800 crashed during a 'belly landing' at Muan International Airport, resulting in at least 62 deaths. The incident involved 181 people and possibly started due to bird strikes affecting the landing gear. Jeju Air, a major South Korean low-cost carrier, has had a strong safety record prior to this.
title: Watch: Moment when plane skidded off runway, burst into flames in South Korea

description: Pushpa 2: The Rule has crossed Rs 1,500 crore globally within 24 days of release, with strong box office figures across its language versions. The Hindi version alone nears Rs 750 crore. Director Sukumar and stars Allu Arjun, Rashmika Mandanna, and Fahadh Faasil are celebrated for their roles, while Allu expressed gratitude for the support at a press event.
title: Pushpa 2 box office collection surpasses Rs 1500 crore

description: Sam Konstas, Australia's young opener, was dismissed by Jasprit Bumrah in the second innings of his Test career on Day 4 of the fourth Test in Melbourne. Australia managed to dismiss the Indian side for 369, taking a 105-run lead. Nitish Kumar Reddy was the last wicket to fall for India, scoring 114. Indian bowlers began their innings with discipline.
title: Bowled! Bumrah ensures Konstas no-show in 2nd innings - Watch

description: Climate activist Sonam Wangchuk visited hunger-striking farmer leader Jagjit Singh Dallewal at the Khanauri border protest site to show solidarity. Dallewal, 70, has been fasting since November 26 to demand a legal guarantee for MSP. The Supreme Court has given Punjab government until December 31 to persuade Dallewal to move to a hospital.
title: 'Food we eat produced by farmers': Sonam Wangchuk meets fasting leader Dallewal

description: India's Koneru Humpy won her second World Rapid Chess Championship title, beating Indonesia's Irene Sukandar. Humpy previously won in 2019. The 37-year-old scored 8.5 points from 11 rounds. Humpy's victory follows D Gukesh's triumph earlier this year, highlighting India's strong performance in chess. Russia's Volodar Murzin clinched the men's title.
title: India's Koneru Humpy becomes Rapid chess world champion

description: A commercial aircraft with 181 people crashed at Muan airport, South Korea. The accident happened during landing when the aircraft encountered birds, causing landing gear problems. 23 individuals were either injured or killed, and evacuation operations are underway with emergency services present at the scene.
title: Plane with 181 on board crashes in South Korea, 29 dead

description: Nitish Reddy's remarkable unbeaten century as India's lower-order batsman, accompanied by his guidance to Mohammed Siraj, bolstered the team's performance in the Boxing Day Test. Former coach Ravi Shastri proposes Reddy's promotion in the batting order to enhance India's balance and strategy for the final Test in Sydney. India's batting has appeared fragile, especially with skipper Rohit Sharma, Virat Kohli, and Rishabh Pant struggling for runs in the five-Test series so far.
title: 'Miyan bhai, ghumega nahi': Nitish Reddy to Mohammed Siraj

description: Australian captain Pat Cummins was puzzled after the third umpire overturned what appeared to be a legitimate dismissal at the MCG. On-field umpire Michael Gough referred a catch to third umpire Sharfuddoula Saikat, who ruled Indian batsman Mohammed Siraj not out. Despite Cummins' request for another review being denied, the match continued, and India finished their innings at 369 runs.
title: Drama at MCG! Cummins denied review on Siraj call

description: Vimal Singh accurately predicted Manmohan Singh's rise to Indian prime ministership, showcasing his foresight and friendship with Singh. Highlighting Singh's humility and accessibility, the article recounts their significant interactions and Singh's leadership during the 2007 Indo-US nuclear deal crisis.
title: ‘You’ll be PM’: A 1997 prophecy that came true in 2004

description: Virat Kohli's 20% match fee penalty for clashing with Australia's Sam Konstas was humorously turned into a traffic discipline lesson by Kerala Police. They posted a viral video reimagining the incident as a traffic scenario, emphasizing the importance of staying in your lane, highlighting that rules apply to everyone, even the celebrated.
title: 'Play by the rules': Kerala Police' take on Kohli-Sam Konstas tiff goes viral

description: RBI has enhanced the functionality of Prepaid Payment Instruments (PPIs) by allowing UPI payments through any third-party UPI-enabled app. Only full-KYC PPIs are eligible for this feature, ensuring added security through pre-authorization. This move promotes digital payments and financial inclusion, making UPI transactions more seamless.
title: RBI has made this 'wallet' change to UPI

description: Bengaluru police have arrested four individuals, including an Axis Bank relationship manager, for allegedly embezzling over Rs 12 crore from Dreamplug Paytech Solutions. The culprits exploited vulnerabilities in Axis Bank's security systems, submitting fake documents and manipulating account details to initiate fraudulent transactions over 14 days.
title: Bengaluru police uncover Rs 12 crore fraud involving bank employee

description: In Bihar's Rohtas district, a police officer, during a confrontation with inebriated men near a railway station, opened fire, resulting in the death of a 32-year-old man, Rana Om Prakash Singh, and injuries to two others. The incident, allegedly sparked by a demand for a bribe, is currently under investigation.
title: Bihar traffic cop shoots dead reveller in 'self-defence'

description: Bangladesh International Crimes Tribunal chief prosecutor Mohammad Tajul Islam stated that trials against top commanders accused of crimes against humanity, including former PM Sheikh Hasina, would be completed within a year. He emphasized priority for Hasina and her subordinates due to their alleged roles in the July-August student-led uprising's killings, aiming for a swift trial process.
title: Trials against accused, including Sheikh Hasina, to be over in a year: ICT

description: Former cricketer Atul Wassan expressed concerns over Rohit Sharma's struggles, attributing it to his decision to bat at number six during the Border-Gavaskar Trophy. This shift in batting position disrupted his rhythm, leading to inconsistent performances. Madan Lal also highlighted Rohit's ongoing difficulty, noting his dismissal while attempting signature shots. Rohit aims to regain form in upcoming innings.
title: 'Made a mistake': Ex-cricketers on Rohit Sharma's poor form
